{#def mngr_forward_origin, trigger_x=0, trigger_y=0, trigger_w=0, trigger_h=38, offset_x=0, offset_y=8 #}
{#
  Standalone sidebar page loaded into the shared modal WebContentsView
  when the user opens the sidebar. The modal view covers the full window
  content area, the body is the transparent backdrop, and the floating
  dark teal panel is pinned at a position derived from the caller's
  trigger geometry. Clicks on the backdrop (anywhere outside the panel)
  dismiss the modal via /_static/sidebar.js; the Escape key is handled
  by main.js's modal before-input-event listener (see openModal in
  electron/main.js), so this page does not install its own Escape
  handler. The panel's height comes from its own flex content -- no JS
  measurement or Electron-side bounds math is needed.

  Position model: the trigger (chrome page's #sidebar-toggle button)
  passes its viewport-relative rect (trigger_x, trigger_y, trigger_w,
  trigger_h) plus a caller-chosen offset (offset_x, offset_y). The menu
  anchors its top-left at the trigger's bottom-left + offset:
    left = trigger_x + offset_x
    top  = trigger_y + trigger_h + offset_y
  Because the chrome view and the modal view share the same window
  coordinate space, the trigger's rect translates directly. The panel
  uses ``py-1.5`` (vertical-only padding) so each row's ``px-2`` (8px)
  internal padding lines up exactly with the trigger button's icon
  offset inside its ``w-8`` shell -- icon columns line up.

  Defaults (no query params): anchor just below a 38px-tall element at
  the top-left of the window, with an 8px gap. That's the right shape
  for the titlebar's first button without any caller customization.

  mngr_forward_origin is exposed via data-mngr-forward-origin so sidebar.js
  can build the cross-origin /goto/<agent>/ URL the plugin serves.
#}
{% set _body_attrs %}data-mngr-forward-origin="{{ mngr_forward_origin }}"{% endset %}
{% set _scripts %}
<script src="/_static/workspace_accent.js" defer></script>
<script src="/_static/sidebar_workspace_row.js" defer></script>
<script src="/_static/sidebar.js" defer></script>
{% endset %}
{% set _menu_left = trigger_x + offset_x %}
{% set _menu_top = trigger_y + trigger_h + offset_y %}
<Base title="Projects"
      body_class="font-sans antialiased bg-transparent"
      body_attrs={{ _body_attrs }}
      scripts={{ _scripts }}>
  <div id="sidebar-backdrop" class="fixed inset-0">
    <div id="sidebar-menu"
         style="left:{{ _menu_left }}px; top:{{ _menu_top }}px;"
         class="absolute w-[244px] flex flex-col gap-px py-1.5 rounded-[10px] border border-white/10 bg-[#0b292b] shadow-[0_12px_32px_rgba(0,0,0,0.25)] overflow-hidden">
      <div id="sidebar-workspaces" class="flex flex-col gap-px"></div>
      <SidebarBottom />
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
